        "monster_family": {
          "name": "Living Topiary",
          "subtype": "monster_family",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        "name": "Living Topiary",
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "Corrupted Topiaries",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 214",
                  "aonid": 276,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 214",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core 2",
                "page": 214,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Most living topiaries are territorial without being actively malevolent; however, when the creation of a living topiary occurs within an area of intense necromantic energy, the topiary can take on a sinister personality. Stories abound of abandoned manors that have corrupted living topiaries prowling their hedge mazes for hapless victims.",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "link": {
              "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 214",
              "aonid": 276,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 214",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Monster Core 2",
            "page": 214,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Topiaries are an extremely common sight across Golarion, especially within the gleaming and well-manicured lawns of nobility. Living topiaries develop from the death of a lone soul in an overgrown area of deep primal magic, with the soul exploding into the plants around it and causing them to grow together into the form of an animal, often influenced by the personality of the dying person. Once fully formed, the living topiary lacks their original memories; however, they're filled with the desire to protect the area they were formed in, driving off invaders and those who would do harm to the flora and fauna.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
